  <section id="location">
    <h3>Location & Jurisdiction</h3>

    <p>
        DPV's location concepts can be utilised to restrict usage of a certain asset to particular location. For this purpose, the [[[LOC]]] extension provides concepts regarding locations such as countries and regions based on the ISO 3166 standards.
    </p>
    <p>
        Furthermore, given that DPV has the relation <code>dpv:hasJurisdiction</code> to represent locations as jurisdictions,when mapping that relation into an ODRL constraint, <code>dpv-odrl:Location</code> can also be used as a left operand
        to indicate jurisdiction.
    </p>

    <table>
        <thead>
