            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="legal">
    <h3>Laws & Legal Bases</h3>

    <p>
        DPV's law and legal basis concepts can be utilised to indicate applicable laws and the legal grounds used to justify a certain processing activity, respectively. For this purpose, the [[[LEGAL]]] extensions provide concepts to represent laws, authorities, and other legal concepts in various jurisdictions.
    </p>

    <p>
        Furthermore, consent controls can be used to require obtaining, providing, withdrawing, refusing, or reaffirming consent, and contract controls to require accepting, negotiating, offering, refusing, and terminating actions associated with a contract.
    </p>

